<HEADLINE> Guatemala Man Kills Wife, Children  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- A man shot and killed a security guard,
his pregnant wife, and three young children after the guard refused
to accept a bribe to cover up the theft of two motorcycles, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Juan Pablo Alcala, 39, was charged late Wednesday with five
counts of murder and one count of attempted murder, said Faustino
Sanchez, spokesman for Guatemala's national police force.
</P>
<P>
   Alcala offered the bribe Tuesday evening at the rural home of
Marcelino Chuy, 37, and opened fire when Chuy refused to take the
money, thought to be $52, Sanchez said.
</P>
<P>
   Among the dead were Chuy's 29-year-old wife, Maria Luisa Monory,
who was eight months pregnant, and their children aged 4, 6 and 18
months. A fourth child, a boy whose age was not released, was in
critical condition Wednesday with several gunshot wounds.
</P>
<P>
   The attack occurred in a tiny village about five miles outside
the colonial tourist town of Antigua, about 25 miles south of
Guatemala City.
</P>
</TEXT>
