<HEADLINE> Dow Is Up 20; Nasdaq Gains 9  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 20 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 7-6 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead nine points and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index is up a little more than a point.
</P>
<P>
   Some Wall Street analysts are looking for a modest improvement
today, after the market had a rough day yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Technology stocks suffered the most, after profit warnings in
the software sector and some negative comments about the computer
chip business.
</P>
<P>
   There have been no such warnings today, clearing the way for a
potential recovery this session.
</P>
<P>
   But, things could also turn cautious today, with little to focus
on other than tomorrow's release of the government's June
employment report.
</P>
