<HEADLINE> Dow, Nasdaq Fall Slightly  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were modestly lower at the start of
trading Thursday as investors remained worried about slumping
corporate profits.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after Wall Street's opening bell, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 13.79 at 10,469.81.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were slightly higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 0.20 at 1,446.43, and the Nasdaq composite
index was down 4.53 at 3,858.57.
</P>
<P>
   With interest rates rising, investors have become worried that
corporate profits will suffer. In Wednesday's session, a flurry of
profit warnings sent technology stocks dramatically lower, and
investors appeared unnerved on Thursday as well.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said it may be difficult for the market to advance
until companies begin reporting actual numbers later this month.
</P>
</TEXT>
