<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 38; Nasdaq Gains 11  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed Thursday as investors remained
worried about slumping corporate profits. Semiconductor stocks
recovered some ground lost in Wednesday's crushing selloff, but
investors remained on edge.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 38.19 at 10,445.41.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were slightly higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 1.40 at 1,447.63, and the Nasdaq composite
index was up 10.80 at 3,873.90.
</P>
<P>
   With interest rates rising, investors have become worried that
corporate profits will suffer. In Wednesday's session, a flurry of
profit warnings sent technology stocks dramatically lower.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday, technology stocks were regaining their balance, but
investors had turned negative toward blue chip names, particularly
the drug stocks that have performed well in recent weeks. Johnson &AMP;
Johnson was down $1.50 to $99.50 and Merck was down $1.25 at
$75.938.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said it may be difficult for the market to advance
until companies begin reporting actual numbers later this month.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 9-to-8 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 116.49 million
shares, behind Wednesday's early pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index fell 0.12 to 518.13.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average fell 0.9 percent. In
afternoon trading, Germany's Xetra DAX index was down 0.2 percent,
Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 0.5 percent, and France's CAC-40 was
down 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ------
