<P>
Two Methodist ministers charged over same-sex rituals
</P>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Complaints have been filed against
United Methodist Church ministers in Maine and Nebraska for
conducting rituals for same-sex couples, the church news service
reports.
</P>
<P>
   In Omaha, charges are pending against the Rev. Mark Kemling for
leading a homosexual union rite June 3. Another Omaha Methodist
minister who led such a ceremony was defrocked last November.
</P>
<P>
   The bishop for New England, Susan Wolfe Hassinger, notified
Brown Memorial United Methodist Church in Clinton, Maine, that
charges were filed against its pastor, the Rev. Susan Davenport,
but have been resolved because she ''asked forgiveness and vows not
to repeat this action.''
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
Reform Jewish synagogues top 900 for the first time
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Reform Judaism's Union of American Hebrew
Congregations has admitted seven new synagogues for a total of 902,
the first time U.S. and Canadian affiliates have exceeded 900.
</P>
<P>
   The new member synagogues are in Florida, Kentucky, Maryland,
New York, Pennsylvania and Washington state. In all, 16
congregations have joined in the past year.
</P>
<P>
   ''Clearly the strength of our programs and the power of our
religious philosophy are important attractions,'' said President
Eric Yoffie.
</P>
<P>
   The union, founded in 1873 by 28 liberal synagogues, reached 600
members by 1960 and passed the 800 mark in 1987.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: www.uahc.org
