<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survivor, Regis, Jesus Win Ratings  </HEADLINE>
By DAVID BAUDER
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Amid the hype about ''Survivor'' and other
reality shows, it was Jesus Christ who quietly proved a formidable
presence in the television ratings last week.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Jennings' news special, ''The Search for Jesus,'' was the
third most-watched prime-time television program last week.
</P>
<P>
   Only CBS' ''Survivor,'' which drew an audience of just under 24
million in its fifth week on the air, and a repeat episode of ''Who
Wants to Be a Millionaire'' drew larger audiences than ''The Search
for Jesus.''
</P>
<P>
   It drew more viewers than any other Jennings special in seven
years and proved somewhat of a surprise to ABC, which postponed it
for a week because the network was concerned the show would compete
against the NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
   ABC also had to be heartened by the continued strength of
''Millionaire.'' Each edition of the game show placed in Nielsen
Media Research's top 10 programs for the week, even though they
were all repeats.
</P>
<P>
   For the week, ABC won with an average of 10 million viewers in
prime-time (6.9 rating, 13 share). CBS had 9.3 million viewers
(6.5, 12), NBC had 8.1 million viewers (5.9, 11) and Fox had 5.8
million (3.9, 7). UPN had 3 million viewers (2.1, 4), the WB had
2.4 million viewers (1.8, 3) and Pax TV had 1.1 million (0.8, 2)
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Nightly News'' won the evening news ratings race with
9.2 million viewers (7.0 rating, 16 share). ABC's ''World News
Tonight'' had 7.9 million viewers (6.2, 14), while the ''CBS
Evening News'' had 7.7 million viewers (5.8, 13).
</P>
<P>
   A rating point represents 1,008,000 households, or 1 percent of
the nation's estimated 100.8 million TV homes. The share is the
percentage of in-use televisions tuned to a given show.
</P>
<P>
   For the week of June 26 to July 2, the top 10 shows, their
networks and ratings were:
</P>
<P>
   ''Survivor,'' CBS, 15.3; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire''
(Tuesday), ABC, 12.9; ''Peter Jennings Reporting: The Search for
Jesus,'' ABC, 11.4; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire''
(Thursday-9:30 p.m.), ABC, 11.3; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire''
(Sunday-9:30 p.m.), ABC, 11.1; ''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire''
(Thursday-9 p.m.), ABC, 9.6; ''Everybody Loves Raymond,'' CBS, 9.3;
''Who Wants to Be a Millionaire'' (Sunday-9 p.m.), ABC, 9.2; ''Law
and Order,'' NBC, 9.1; ''20/20 Downtown,'' ABC, 8.4.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: http://www.nielsenmedia.com
</P>
</TEXT>
