<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Rattles Nicaragua  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) -- A strong earthquake shook Nicaragua on
Thursday, destroying more than a dozen homes. There were
unconfirmed reports of several deaths and injuries.
</P>
<P>
   The quake, with a preliminary magnitude of 5.9, struck at 1:30
p.m. and was centered in Laguna de Apoyo, about 30 miles east of
the capital of Managua.
</P>
<P>
   It was felt across the country as far away as Waslala, in the
northeast of the country and in the province of Jinotega, on the
border with Honduras.
</P>
<P>
   In San Juan de Oriente, 35 miles east of the capital, residents
told state Radio Nicaragua that at least 15 houses were destroyed
and that there were some deaths and injuries. The radio station
also said the quake took down a wall of a church in the town.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue officials were en route to the scene.
</P>
