<HEADLINE> House Member Halts Ship Transfer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A House committee chairman has halted the
transfer of a ship to the Dominican Republican until that Caribbean
nation extradites the accused killer of a New York City police
officer.
</P>
<P>
   ''The government of the Dominican Republic has assured me on
several occasions that it will not allow its territory to be used
as a refuge for criminals,'' Rep. Benjamin Gilman, chairman of the
International Relations Committee, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
