<HEADLINE> Flyers Sign Tocchet, Sykora  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Flyers re-signed right wing
Rick Tocchet to a two-year contract Thursday and signed Czech
defenseman Michael Sykora to a multiyear deal.
</P>
<P>
   ''Philly was my first choice because it's a good fit for me. The
chemistry is right for me,'' said Tocchet, who was an unrestricted
free agent. ''We were two minutes from going to the Stanley Cup
finals, so I'm excited about next year's team.''
</P>
<P>
   Tocchet, 36, rejoined the team in a March trade with Phoenix. He
had three goals and three assists in 16 regular-season games for
the Flyers, and five goals and six assists in 18 playoff games.
</P>
<P>
   He has 426 goals and 486 assists in 16 seasons with the Flyers,
Pittsburgh, Los Angeles, Boston, Washington and Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   Sykora, 27, had 11 goals and 14 assists in 48 games last season
for Sparta Praha of the Czech League. The 6-foot-5, 225-pound
defenseman has 10 goals and 43 assists in 218 NHL games with San
Jose, Chicago and Tampa Bay.
</P>
