<HEADLINE> Multiple Deaths Probed in Ontario  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Police said Thursday they discovered six homicide
victims -- a man and woman and their four young children -- at a
house in a quiet southern Ontario neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they weren't seeking any suspects, but refused
comment on speculation the killings were committed by one of the
six who then committed suicide.
</P>
<P>
   ''There was trauma to the bodies. I won't speak to the cause of
death at this point,'' Staff Sgt. Brent Thomlinson said.
</P>
<P>
   But few other details about the victims or what happened were
released almost 12 hours after the discovery in Kitchener, 60 miles
west of Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   Thomlinson said police needed to notify next of kin and figure
out what happened before providing details. Neighbors described the
victims as a young couple with children ages 6, 5, 2, and less than
a year.
</P>
<P>
   Police said autopsies would be conducted Friday in Hamilton,
Ontario.
</P>
<P>
   The parents of the deceased father owned the house and lived on
the property in a trailer parked in the driveway, according to
neighbors. They said the family originally came from Eastern Europe
and moved to Canada in recent years, living in different places
until moving in with the grandparents in the last six months.
</P>
<P>
   One of the grandparents entered the house and saw the body of
one victim, then called police to report that someone was injured,
according to media reports. The grandparents left the house later
Thursday with police.
</P>
<P>
   Throughout the day, residents of the tree-lined neighborhood
gathered outside the suburban, two-story house to console each
other and try to learn what happened.
</P>
<P>
   They spoke of a young family facing financial problems. A local
social worker confirmed his agency once visited the family because
it received concerned calls regarding how the children were living,
but found nothing wrong.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a tragedy,'' said neighbor Roberta Butler. ''They (the
children) were just our here playing last night.''
</P>
</TEXT>
