<HEADLINE> Phillies Minor Leaguers Injured  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Philadelphia Phillies minor league pitchers
Matt Beech and Ryan Nye were injured in an automobile accident
Thursday morning while driving to the team's training facility in
Clearwater, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Beech, 28, was driving and Nye, 27, was a front-seat passenger.
Beech's Ford Explorer was stopped at a traffic light when another
vehicle changed lanes and rear-ended their sport utility vehicle,
according to reports.
</P>
<P>
   Both were taken to Bayfront Medical Center in St. Petersburg.
Beech was removed on a backboard and head brace, and was said to be
experiencing back pain. He was scheduled to be held overnight and
undergo an MRI test.
</P>
<P>
   Nye had an X-ray taken of his neck, and was discharged later in
the day.
</P>
<P>
   Beech, a left-hander, and Nye, a right-hander, are each
rehabbing from surgeries late last season. Neither has pitched in
the majors since 1998.
</P>
