<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 16 Hurt on German Cable Car  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KEMPTEN, Germany (AP) -- A gondola carrying hikers to the top of
the 7,218-foot Nebelhorn peak crashed into a guide rail Thursday,
injuring 16 people, some seriously, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Several of the injured were taken to hospitals by helicopter,
and other helicopters were helping to evacuate 500 climbers from
the top of the mountain.
</P>
<P>
   The accident was the first for the gondola company in its 70
years of operation, said Augustin Kroells, a member of the board of
operators. The accident was at the second of three stations along
the 4-mile gondola line.
</P>
<P>
   It was not immediately clear if the accident was caused by
mechanical failure or human error.
</P>
</TEXT>
