<HEADLINE> Mother gets 25 to life in baby slaying  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - A 24-year-old woman convicted of killing her
baby by slamming her head against a wall up to 60 times was
sentenced to 25 years to life in prison Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Renee Mitchell was found guilty in late May of killing
3-month-old Ana Marie in July 1999 when the girl would not stop
crying. The baby, injured so badly a pathologist could not count
the number of fractures she received, died the day after the
beating.
</P>
<P>
   The little girl suffered brain injuries consistent with those
caused by a high-speed car crash - not with falling off a couch,
the first explanation Mitchell gave police.
</P>
<P>
   At trial, Mitchell changed her story, saying her statement to
police was coerced and the baby must have been killed by either her
boyfriend or her 2-year-old son. Police ruled out the boyfriend and
son as suspects.
</P>
