<SUBHEAD>
Airline Workers Denounce Air Rage
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Airline employees handed out leaflets and demonstrated
at airports around the world today to demand that more be done to stop the rise
of ''air rage'' among passengers. Unions representing flight attendants and
ground crews decried passengers whose misbehavior ranges from being noisy to
becoming downright violent. The Transport Workers Federation, an umbrella
organization for the unions, said air rage incidents increased from 1,132 in
1994 to 5,416 in 1997.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Episcopal Church Eyes Lutheran Ties
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Episcopal Church members are considering an alliance with the
country's largest Lutheran denomination, a move that leaders said would be a big
step forward for Christians. The plan is expected to come to a vote tomorrow at
the Episcopalians' General Convention. If approved, the Episcopal and
Evangelical Lutheran churches would share each other's sacraments and clergy,
and cooperate in missionary projects and other ventures. The churches would have
a combined 7.5 million members.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Gore Chides Bush on Kids' Health
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Vice President Al Gore accused GOP presidential rival Gov.
George W. Bush of neglecting poor children at home in Texas because the state
could lose $449 million in federal funding for a children's health insurance
program. ''Such oversight is consistent with Gov. George Bush's neglect for
children without health insurance in Texas,'' the Gore campaign said today.
Texas is among dozens of states that have not yet used all the federal funds
allotted them.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Starr Aide Is Charged Over Leaks
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Kenneth Starr's former spokesman is to stand trial next
week for criminal contempt in a case involving news leaks during the Monica
Lewinsky investigation. Charles Bakaly faces trial over statements he made in
connection with investigations into alleged leaks from the special prosecutor's
office, according to court documents. Bakaly is being prosecuted before U.S.
District Judge Norma Holloway Johnson.
</P>
