JFK Jr. Is Blamed for Crash
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- John F. Kennedy Jr. probably became confused in the night
sky of Martha's Vineyard, Mass., leading to the private plane crash that killed
him, his wife and her sister, federal investigators said today. The National
Transportation Safety Board said Kennedy's piloting difficulties were likely to
have been caused by ''spatial disorientation.''
</P>
