<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Sox 8, Twins 7  </HEADLINE>
By JASON WOLF
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Nomar Garciaparra hit two two-run homers and
Paxton Crawford, in just his second major league start, outpitched
Minnesota's Brad Radke as Boston beat the Twins 8-7 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Crawford (1-1) gave up one run on six hits through seven innings
to help the Red Sox complete a four-game sweep. Boston scored 44
runs in the series.
</P>
<P>
   Radke (5-10) was making his first start since agreeing Monday to
a four-year, $36 million contract, the richest deal in the Twins'
history. He pitched seven innings and gave up eight runs on seven
hits in his worst outing of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Radke allowed two-run homers in the first, third and sixth
innings. He had gone four starts without giving up a homer.
</P>
<P>
   Garciaparra was 2-for-4 with four RBIs in his first two-homer
game this season and the 12th of his career. He's hitting .404
(19-for-47) in his last 11 games.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Daubach was also 2-for-4 with four RBIs for the Red Sox.
</P>
<P>
   It was the fifth straight loss for the Twins, who have lost 12
of their last 19.
</P>
<P>
   Carl Everett walked in the sixth and Garciaparra hit the next
pitch for his second homer of the game, his 10th this year, into
the left-field bleachers.
</P>
<P>
   Garciaparra's home run in the first inning, which gave Boston a
2-0 lead, was the first homer given up by Radke since June 16
against the Mariners.
</P>
<P>
   The Twins cut the lead to 2-1 in the first, when Midre Cummings,
who led off the game with a single, scored on Ron Coomer's
sacrifice fly.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota scored four runs in the bottom of the ninth, including
a two-run shot by David Ortiz, his second home run in as many
nights.
</P>
<P>
   Cristian Guzman was 4-for-5 for Minnesota with two RBIs.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Red Sox outfielder Troy O'Leary left the game with one out
in the eighth after colliding with Garciaparra while trying to
field a fly ball. Garciaparra's shoulder smashed into O'Leary's
chest and both were on the ground for a few moments before O'Leary
walked off. ... It was the first time this season Radke gave up
more than two homers in a start. ... The Red Sox improved to 7-0
against the Twins this season. ... Guzman got thrown out at second
base by about four steps in the third when he tried tagging up on
Matt Lawton's fly ball to center field. ... Crawford, who spent all
of 1998 and 1999 at Double A Trenton, spent just over a month at
Triple-A Pawtucket this season before being promoted to the majors
July 1, the day he made his major league debut in a 7-2 loss to the
White Sox.
</P>
</TEXT>
