<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 23:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Loses Toes Crossing Tracks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOUNT PROSPECT, Ill. (AP) -- A woman lost the toes on her right
foot after she crawled under a commuter railcar in an attempt to
cross the tracks and catch the train.
</P>
<P>
   When the Metra train pulled into the Mount Prospect station in
suburban Chicago on Monday, Jennifer Padulo, 25, and her friend
Danielle Huculak found they were on the wrong side of the tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Huculak ducked underneath the train and Padulo followed. She
scampered to the other side as the train started moving but her
foot didn't clear the steel wheels.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was lucky it was only my foot under there, or it could have
been a huge disaster,'' Padulo said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Huculak was not hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Davis, spokesman for Union Pacific, which runs Metra's
Northwest line, said there have been a number of injuries and
deaths caused by people crawling under, over and around trains.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
